4 otolaryngologist who is certified by the American Board of
5 Otolaryngology and one lay member.
6 B. The members of the original Board shall serve the following
7 terms: one member for one (1) year, two members for two (2) years,
8 and two members for three (3) years. Thereafter, at the expiration
9 of the term, or termination of the member’s service for any reason,
10 the Governor shall appoint each successor for a term of three (3)
11 years, or for the remainder of an unexpired term. The successor for
12 any of the three speech-language pathologists or audiologists will
13 be selected from a list of five licensed speech-language
14 pathologists or audiologists, furnished by the Oklahoma Speech-
15 Language-Hearing Association In selecting appointees, the Governor
16 may consider recommendations from a statewide organization
17 representing speech-language pathologists or audiologists, a state
18 chapter of a national organization representing speech-language
19 pathologists or audiologists, or other groups or individuals in this
20 state. The re-creation of the Board shall not affect the staggered
21 terms of office for Board members established with the original
22 Board.
